# Website — Pitch Deck Site

## What it is

A single-page static site styled as a story scroll pitch deck. The audience is potential collaborators, builders, partners — NOT end-user customers. The goal is making the project instantly understandable.

## Tech stack

Vanilla HTML + CSS + JS. No build tools. No frameworks. No dependencies beyond Google Fonts. The entire site is one `index.html` file deployed to GitHub Pages.

## Design system

- **Display font:** Fraunces (variable, optical sizing) — warm, wonky serif
- **Body font:** DM Sans — clean geometric sans
- **Mono font:** JetBrains Mono — for slide numbers and labels

### Colors

Dark sections: `--dark-bg: #0f0e0c`, `--dark-fg: #f5f0e6`, `--dark-accent: #e8a830`
Light sections: `--light-bg: #f5f0e6`, `--light-fg: #1a1714`, `--light-accent: #b8432a`

### Layout

- Full-viewport sections (min-height: 100vh), alternating dark/light
- One idea per section, big headlines, minimal text
- Slide numbers in monospace (01, 02, 03...)
- Scroll-triggered fade-in animations via IntersectionObserver
- Staggered animation on list items via `.stagger` class

